<body>
  <div class="header">
    <h1>WALES EVICTION ROADMAP</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Renting Homes (Wales) Act 2016 - Step by Step Guide</p>
  </div>

  <p><strong>Property:</strong> {{property.full_address}}</p>
  <p><strong>Contract-Holder:</strong> {{tenant.full_name}}</p>
  <p><strong>Notice Type:</strong> {{#if (eq notice.route 'wales_section_173')}}Section 173 (No-Fault){{else}}Fault-Based (Section 157/159/161/162){{/if}}</p>

  <hr>

  <div class="step">
    <span class="step-number">1</span>
    <span class="step-title">Verify Your Compliance</span>
    <div class="step-content">
      <p>Before serving any notice, ensure you meet ALL requirements:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>‚òê Registered with <strong>Rent Smart Wales</strong></li>
        <li>‚òê Deposit protected in approved scheme (if taken)</li>
        <li>‚òê Written statement of occupation contract provided</li>
        <li>‚òê All required documents given to contract-holder</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="warning">
        <strong>‚ö†Ô∏è Critical:</strong> You cannot serve a valid Section 173 notice without Rent Smart Wales registration.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="step">
    <span class="step-number">2</span>
    <span class="step-title">Serve Your Notice</span>
    <div class="step-content">
      <p>Serve the notice correctly:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Hand delivery (keep detailed notes)</li>
        <li>First class post (add 2 working days to notice period)</li>
        <li>Leave at property in prominent position</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="timeline">
        <strong>Notice Period:</strong>
        {{#if (eq notice.route 'wales_section_173')}}
          Minimum 6 months (Section 173 no-fault)
        {{else}}
          Varies by ground - check your notice for specific period
        {{/if}}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="step">
    <span class="step-number">3</span>
    <span class="step-title">Wait for Notice Period to Expire</span>
    <div class="step-content">
      <p>During this time:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Document any further breaches</li>
        <li>Keep records of all communication</li>
        <li>Prepare your evidence bundle</li>
        <li>Consider if contract-holder may vacate voluntarily</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="tip">
        <strong>üí° Tip:</strong> Many contract-holders leave before court proceedings. Maintain communication.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="step">
    <span class="step-number">4</span>
    <span class="step-title">Apply to Court</span>
    <div class="step-content">
      <p>If contract-holder hasn't vacated:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Complete Form N5 (standard possession) or Form N5B (accelerated - Section 173 only)</li>
        <li>Prepare Form N119 (Particulars of Claim)</li>
        <li>Pay court fee (currently ¬£355 online, ¬£391 paper)</li>
        <li>File at your local County Court</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="timeline">
        <strong>Timeline:</strong> Court hearing typically 4-8 weeks after filing
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="step">
    <span class="step-number">5</span>
    <span class="step-title">Attend Court Hearing</span>
    <div class="step-content">
      <p>For standard possession claims:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Bring all original documents</li>
        <li>Bring proof of Rent Smart Wales registration</li>
        <li>Bring evidence of deposit protection</li>
        <li>Prepare to answer questions from District Judge</li>
      </ul>
      <p><em>Note: Accelerated procedure (N5B) usually decided on papers without hearing.</em></p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="step">
    <span class="step-number">6</span>
    <span class="step-title">Obtain Possession Order</span>
    <div class="step-content">
      <p>If successful, court grants possession order:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Usually 14 days for contract-holder to vacate</li>
        <li>Can be extended to 42 days in exceptional circumstances</li>
        <li>Order specifies exact date possession required</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="step">
    <span class="step-number">7</span>
    <span class="step-title">Enforcement (If Needed)</span>
    <div class="step-content">
      <p>If contract-holder still refuses to leave:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Apply for Warrant of Possession (Form N325)</li>
        <li>Pay bailiff fee (currently ¬£130)</li>
        <li>County Court Bailiff will attend to evict</li>
        <li>You may attend but cannot assist physically</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="warning">
        <strong>‚ö†Ô∏è Never:</strong> Attempt to physically remove the contract-holder yourself - this is illegal.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="footer">
    <p>Generated by Landlord Heaven | www.landlordheaven.co.uk</p>
    <p>This guide is for information only and does not constitute legal advice.</p>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
